{
  "answer": "The ghazal is Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, chapter 213 (\"baazeecha-e-atfaal hai duniya mere aage\").\n\n> The fabled throne of Solomon is but a piece of play,  \n> The Savior's miracle, a word I brush away.[^1]\n\n> My Faith holds back, while Heresy would have its way;  \n> The Kaaba's at my back, the Church is on display.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-411662).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/213-baazeecha-e-atfaal-hai-duniya-mere-aage/translation/#p-dfc2f3).",
